# docs/ — source of truth for {{PROJECT_NAME}}

This directory is the **contract**, not commentary. Behavior, schema, routes, and UI
are specified here first; code implements them. When docs and code disagree, that is a
bug to report — never silently pick one (`CLAUDE.md` → Doc-code parity).

## Layout

| Dir | Holds |
| --- | --- |
| `business/` | What the product does, per feature: rules, flows, edge cases, glossary, status. |
| `contracts/` | The hard interfaces: error taxonomy, type catalog, code style, per-entity use-case + repository contracts. |
| `database/` | Schema, migrations, storage boundaries. |
| `decision-tables/` | Every testable branch as a row → maps 1:1 to a test. |
| `state/` | State-management / provider contracts. |
| `ui-ux/` | UI contract, wireframes, copy. |
| `testing/` | Test strategy and the bug-CLASS gate map. |
| `quality/` | Performance + observability contracts. |
| `project-management/` | The WBS (task source of truth) + commit traceability log. |
| `checklist/` | Implementation + review checklists. |
| `agent/` | Task template + sub-agent orchestration rules. |
| `_generated/` | Tool output (repo-map). Do not hand-edit. |

Start at `docs/MANIFEST.md` for the full file index, or `docs/business/index.md` for behavior.
